President Cyril Ramphosa will address soldiers and the police before they are deployed for the lockdown on Thursday. Ramaphosa will likely outline the importance of the mission and what’s expected of them. • Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramphosa will address soldiers and the police before they are deployed for the lockdown on Thursday. Ramaphosa will likely outline the importance of the mission and what’s expected of them. The soldiers will be joining their police counterparts on the frontline to enforce the lockdown. COVID-19: Ramaphosa calls for National Day of Prayer President Cyril Ramaphosa is calling on all South Africans to observe two-minutes of prayer or silent meditation. The national day of prayer will be held on the eve of the 21-day national lockdown. Ramaphosa says the prayer should be held between 18:00 and 18:30 on Thursday.